      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 28/3/81. ¶ W. H. Odgers Esqr ¶ Undersecretary. ¶ Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.03.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">U81/2810, unit 1271, VPRS 3991 inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/3/81.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">W. H. Odgers Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Undersecretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In accordance with your request I have the honor to make an official application for such Governments publications, as the hon. the Chief Secretary may be pleased to grant to the distinguished naturalist-traveller, Baron N. de Miklouho-Maclay, who waited on you this day. This Gentleman received also from the Gov. Printing-office in Sydney all the scientific works issued there, and solicits for the furtherance of his studies from the Victorian Government the works of Prof M'Coy, Mr Smyth, Mr Ellery and myself, so far as they pertain to science, also Mr Hayter's summary of <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>statistic<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Hayter (1875)?</p>
               </note> and Mr Skeens general map of Australia<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Skene &amp; Slight (1879), or the updated edition, Skene &amp; Slight (1880); see Darragh (2001a).</p>
               </note> and special map of Victoria.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Skene (1872).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your very obedient,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The Chief Secretary, Graham Berry, approved M's proposal, and on 13 April Robert S. Brain from the Government Printing Office wrote to the Chief Secretary's Office: </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>One Copy of each of the following publications will be forwarded to Baron Maclay tomorrow: —</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Smyth's Aborigines</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mueller's Fragmenta Vols 6. 7. 8. 9. 10.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>"<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Botanic Teachings</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>"<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Select Plants</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>"<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Native Plants</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>"<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Eucalyptographia (Decades 1 to 7 inclusive)</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>McCoy's Zoology — 5 Decades</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>McCoy's Palaeontology, Ellery's works, Statistics, and the maps can be obtained from the Mines Department, the Observatory, the Government Statist, and the Lands Department respectively</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.8264in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Baron Maclay called here today and requested me to mention that as he contemplates leaving the Colony very shortly he would be obliged if these Publications could be sent to him, as soon as possible. [This paragraph is marked with a line and the note: 'Urgent'.]</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On the same day memoranda were forwarded to the Departments of Mines and Lands and to the Government Astronomer. Odgers also sent a note marked 'Urgent' to T. Couchman, Secretary for Mines, asking him to provide a copy of McCoy's Palaeontology, which Couchman sent the next day. A letter was sent to Miklouho-Maclay on 23 April, after his address had been obtained from M (see T. Wilson to M, 20 April 1881).</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 25 May 1881 E. M. Paul, the Russian Consul in New South Wales [i.e. Edmund Monson Paul] wrote to the Chief Secretary thanking him, on behalf of Miklouho-Maclay, for 'the various Government Publications and Maps you were good enough to send him'.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to W. Odgers, 22 April 1881 and T. Wilson to M, 10 May 1881.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
